          • [ - ] blackbird - member since 18-Aug-18

            @realnews You score three goals, you're going to get MotM. It's an algorithm that decides, not a person picking. I think what's impressive about Neymar is that he did not score a hattrick but was only 0.1 behind Cavani in his rating. Right there that tells you how much he contributes. because having such a high ranking when some other guy scores 3 goals and another player got 2 assists is incredibly rare. He's amazing, but he doesn't need to get MotM every time. (By the way, to score a "tap-in," you need to know how to position yourself, and Cavani is one of the best at that. There's no need to shit on Cavani's achievement to talk about Neymar's vision. Plus, you shoot yourself in the foot the moment Neymar scores a tap-in, which he does frequently because he's ALSO excellent at getting into the box unmarked.)
